subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to
H. ishigakus
Belokobylskij & Maeto , 2009 from Japan (Ryukyus), but differs from the later by having the ocelli large, POL 1.3 x Od and 0.7 x OOL (small, POL 0.8-1.0 x Od and 0.35-0.40 x OOL in
H. ishigakus
), occipital carina not joined ventrally with hypostomal carina (joined at least by additional carina in
H. ishigakus
), metacarp 1.25 x longer than pterostigma (1.1 x in
H. ishigakus
), suture between second and third metasomal tergites weakly sinuate (distinctly sinuate in
H. ishigakus
), median length of second tergite 0.5 x its basal width (0.35-0.40 x in
H. ishigakus
), and ovipositor sheath shorter, 0.5 x as long as metasoma and 0.3 x as long as fore wing (longer, 0.8-1.0 x as long as metasoma and 0.45-0.55 x as long as fore wing in
H. ishigakus
).
